# Legacy agent sync (Cursor / iOS)

You own **`ios/**`**. Claude Code owns **`backend/**`**. Full protocol: `docs/engineering/AGENT_WORKFLOW.md`.

## Session start (mandatory)

1. `git status` + read `tasks.json` (open `decisions[]`, **`question`/`concern`/`idea` threads**, `owner: "ios"` tasks)
2. **Reply** to threads where `needs: "ios"` or backend raised something you have not answered
3. Read **last 2 entries** in `docs/engineering/collab-log.md` + **Backend → iOS** section
4. If API work: read `docs/engineering/api-contract.md`

Chat is **not** authoritative — only repo docs.

## Cross-agent feedback (required)

- **Raise** concerns/questions/ideas in `tasks.json` → `decisions[]` (set `needs: "backend"` when appropriate)
- **Reply** via `responses[]` with `"author": "ios"` before session end
- Encouraged: flag privacy/UX risks as `kind: "concern"` even when non-blocking

## Edit boundaries

- Primary: `ios/**`
- Do not edit `backend/**` without a collab-log + dashboard thread
- Update `tasks.json` when marking tasks done or posting thread replies

## Session end

Append `[ios → all] YYYY-MM-DD — …` to `collab-log.md`. All open threads needing iOS must have your reply.

## Truth hierarchy

`tasks.json` > `collab-log.md` > `api-contract.md` > chat > Ruflo
